    "created_at": "2015-03-25T16:31:28Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-03-25T16:31:28Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Agreed, for publications or important presentations it is better to save the figure to file. \n\nBut for quick and dirty presentations, I find it extremely useful to just be able to copy/paste the results from the notebook. One great thing about the notebook is that one doesn't have to come up with figure names and output directories anymore. Plus, others who only have access to the html version, can select figures to extract and add to presentations. \n"
